<span class="header1">Business/Management paired with
Clerical/Administrative (CD)</span>

<p>If you had a high score in categories "C" and "D" you have a head
for business. You are a good thinker and know how to get what you
want. You are probably goal-oriented and prefer to know what you are
working toward.  You may be an outgoing person who likes to lead, or
you may be a quiet person who likes working with numbers. Either
way, you know how get the job done. You will benefit from learning
to understand business.</p>
<p>Most occupations in this pairing require a bachelor's degree.
Many others require some post-high school courses.  In most of the
occupations listed under this pairing, the more education you have
the better your chances of employment. The competition for these
jobs is tough. You will need to give yourself every advantage
possible.</p>
