<span class="header1">BUSINESS SALES</span>
<p>People who do well in this occupation are self-starters and can
be responsible for their own schedule.  In addition, they like
meeting new people.  If this describes you, consider the occupations
in this field.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Insurance Agent</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/C506005.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Insurance Agent" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An insurance agent sells and services insurance
policies.  People buy insurance for their homes, cars, and even
health.  It protects them from losing a lot of money if something
happens to their possessions or themselves.  But choosing the right
insurance can be difficult.  As an insurance agent, you would help
people decide what type of insurance policy they need. You would
also help them to file a claim to collect money on their policy when
necessary.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>For insurance sales agent jobs, many companies
and independent agencies prefer to hire college graduates -
especially those who have majored in business or economics. High
school graduates may be hired if they have proven sales ability or
have been successful in other types of work.  A state license is
required.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of insurance agents was
$50,940 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Travel Agent</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1216.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Travel Agent">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>When people go on trips, they often make
transportation and hotel reservations. A travel agent is important
to a traveler. If you were a travel agent, you would work very
closely with the public making arrangements for vacations or
business trips. You might work for a hotel or an airline. A good
agent must be able to work well with people and understand the needs
of a traveler.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>The minimum requirement for those interested in
becoming a travel agent is a high school diploma or equivalent. Much
of the training is provided on the job, a significant part of which
consists of instruction on how to use reservation systems. Training
specific to becoming a travel agent is available at many
vocational schools, online, and in community colleges. A few
colleges offer bachelor's or master's degrees in travel and tourism.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of travel agents was
$40,660 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Cashier</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1142.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Cashier">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A cashier takes the money of customers who want
to buy something from a store.  As a cashier, you would ring up the
items the customer wanted to buy. You would handle cash, checks, and
credit and debit card purchases. It would be important that the
amount of money in the cash drawer matched the amount on the
receipts in the machine.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>If you were a cashier you would be given on-the-
job training.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of cashiers was $23,650
in May 2019. </blockquote>

