<span class="header1">BUSINESS FINANCIAL</span>
<p>People who do well in the occupations in this field enjoy working
with money. They also are good organizers and can keep track of
details.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Loan Officer</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/C506008.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Loan Officer">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A loan officer works for a bank or lending
company. As a loan officer, you help customers fill out loan
applications and make sure that the information on the application
is correct. You would then see if the people wanting the loan met
your company's guidelines for a loan. If so, you would help to
process the loan.  If not, you would help them to understand why
they did not get the loan.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Loan officers usually need a bachelor's degree
in finance, economics, or a related field. Those who work with home loans must be licensed. Previous banking,
lending, or sales experience is also highly valued by
employers.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of loan officers was
$63,270 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Bookkeeper</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1287.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Bookkeeper">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>All companies must keep detailed records of
their cash flow and how much money they earn. As a bookkeeper, you
would be responsible for keeping this information. You would have to
enjoy working with numbers and be good at keeping track of details
to do this job well.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job.
Most companies offer on-the-job training. Courses in business math
and computer science from a vocational school can help you to get a
job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of bookkeepers was
$41,230 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Bank Teller</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CD/1371.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Bank Teller">
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A bank teller handles large sums of money. As a
bank teller, you would help customers with their deposits and
withdrawals. Banks look for people who work well with customers,
have good math skills, and know the importance of keeping detailed
records.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A high school diploma is needed to be a bank
teller. A teller is given on-the-job training.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of bank tellers was
$31,230 in May 2019. </blockquote>

